725928f-a.title: Queens: 159th Street - Evans Avenue
725928f-a.text:
159th Street, west side, north from Evans Road, showing
homes that were typical of old Jamaica. 159th Street was for-
merly Prospect Street, and Evans Road was formerly Catherine
Street, a short, crooked thoroughfare. Evans Road is now an
appendage to Liberty Avenue, the rest of Catherine Street having
been widened and renamed Liberty Avenue.
P. L. Sperr  March 30, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS
